don, Manitoba|Brandon]] and [[Portage la Prairie, Manitoba|Portage la Prairie]]. It surrounds the independently governed [[Carberry, Manitoba|Town of Carberry]] and includes the unincorporated communities of Brookdale, Wellwood and Edrans. Also located in the former RM of North Cypress are the Acadia, Fairway and Riverbend [[Hutterite]] [[Hutterite#Colonies|colonies]]. The former RM has connections to the [[Manitoba Highway 1|Trans Canada Highway]] (which runs directly through North Cypress), as well as [[Manitoba Highway 5|Highway 5]] and PR 351.\n\n=== Communities ===\n<div style=\"float:left;width:33%;\">\n* [[Brookdale, Manitoba|Brookdale]]\n* [[Edrans, Manitoba|Edrans]]\n* [[Fairview, Manitoba|Fairview]]\n* [[Firdale, Manitoba|Firdale]]\n* [[Gregg, Manitoba|Gregg]]\n* [[Harte, Manitoba|Harte]]\n* [[Ingelow, Manitoba|Ingelow]]\n</div><div style=\"float:left;width:33%;\">\n* [[Melbourne, Manitoba|Melbourne]]\n* [[Oberon, Manitoba|Oberon]]\n* [[Onah, Manitoba|Onah]]\n* [[Petrel, Manitoba|Petrel]]\n* [[Pleasant Point, Manitoba|Pleasant Point]]\n* [[Shilo, Manitoba|Shilo]]\n* [[Wellwood, Manitoba|Wellwood]]\n</div>{{clear}}\n\n== Economy ==\nThe former RM's economy benefits from its location along the [[Manitoba Highway 1|Trans Canada Highway]] as well as access to both the [[Canadian Pacific Railway|Canadian Pacific]] and [[Canadian National Railway|Canadian National]] rail lines, close proximity to [[Brandon, Manitoba|Brandon]] and direct route to [[Winnipeg]]. The former RM is set upon rich sandy soil, and is widely known for potatoes which are grown by local farming operations. The former RM is also known for forests of [[spruce]], [[Populus|poplar]] and aspen oak trees, and the Carberry sandhills. It is also home to several major employers including [[McCain Foods]] and ADM Agri Industries. The Manitoba Crop Diversification Centre (MCDC) is also located in the former RM of North Cypress.\n\n== Services ==\nEmergency services are provided by the [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]], the Carberry/North Cypress Fire Department, and the Carberry & District Health Centre.\n\nSchools are overseen by the [[Beautiful Plains School Division]], and include R.J. Waugh Elementary School and Carberry Collegiate Institute in [[Carberry, Manitoba|Carberry]], Brookdale Elementary School in Brookdale, and several small [[Hutterite]] [[Hutterite#Education|colony schools]] located on the Acadia, Fairway and Riverbend [[Hutterite|Hutterite colonies]].\n\n== Wildlife ==\nThe area is home to many species of wildlife including some protected and [[endangered species]]. [[White-tailed deer]], [[moose]], [[elk]], [[great horned owl]], [[snowy owl]], [[gray wolf]], [[canadian lynx]], [[peregrine falcon]], [[coyote]] and the rare [[skink]] are a few of the animal species that are found within the former RM. Although not common, [[American Black Bear|American black bears]], [[bobcat]]s and [[Cougar|pumas]] are also routinely spotted in the area.\n\nBecause of the unique ecosystem and large forests, there are several large parcels of [[crown land]] and protected land areas within the former RM of North Cypress, including a large part of the [[Provincial forests (Manitoba)|Spruce Woods Provincial Forest]], and a small part of [[Spruce Woods Provincial Park]].\n\n== Military ==\nThe former RM was home to two major [[Canadian Forces]] installations, [[Camp Hughes]] and [[RCAF Station Carberry]].\n\n== See also ==\n*[[Camp Hughes]]\n*[[RCAF Station Carberry]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n* [http://www12.statcan.ca/english/census06/data/profiles/community/Details/Page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=CSD&Code1=4607065&Geo2=PR&Code2=46&Data=Count&SearchText=North%20Cypress&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&GeoLevel=&GeoCode=4607065 Statistics Canada North Cypress Profile]\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://www.rmofnorthcypress.ca RM of North Cypress] \n*[http://geodepot.statcan.ca/GeoSearch2006/GeoSearch2006.jsp?resolution=H&lang=E&otherLang=F&census=Yes&DisplayData=Ye