{"title_page": "Rural Municipality of Wallace", "text_new": "The '''Rural Municipality of Wallace''' is a former [[rural municipality]] (RM) in the [[Canada|Canadian]] [[Provinces and territories of Canada|province]] of Manitoba. It was originally incorporated as a rural municipality on December 22, 1883.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/municipalities/rural.shtml | title=Manitoba\u2019s Municipal History: Rural Municipalities and Local Government Districts | publisher=The Manitoba Historical Society | date=September 21, 2014 | accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref> It ceased on January 1, 2015 as a result of its [[Manitoba municipal amalgamations, 2015|provincially mandated]] [[Merger (politics)|amalgamation]] with the [[Rural Municipality of Woodworth|RM of Woodworth]] and the [[Elkhorn, Manitoba|Village of Elkhorn]] to form the [[Rural Municipality of Wallace \u2013 Woodworth]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/municipalities/amalgamations.shtml | title=Manitoba\u2019s Municipal History: Municipal Amalgamations (2015) | publisher=The Manitoba Historical Society | date=December 1, 2014 | accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe former RM surrounds the [[Virden, Manitoba|Town of Virden]].\n\n== Communities ==\n* [[Hargrave, Manitoba|Hargrave]]\n* [[Harmsworth, Manitoba|Harmsworth]]\n* [[Kirkella, Manitoba|Kirkella]]\n* [[Kola, Manitoba|Kola]]\n* [[Maples, Manitoba|Maples]]\n* [[Two Creeks, Manitoba|Two Creeks]]\n\n== Reeves ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name\n! In Office\n|-\n| [[Adam Gerrond McDougall]]\n| 1884\u20131887\n|-\n| [[James Frame|James Findlay Frame]]\n| 1888\u20131891\n|-\n| William M. Cushing\n| 1892\n|-\n| [[Watson Montgomery Crosby]]\n| 1893\u20131896\n|-\n| George A. Freeman\n| 1897\u20131899\n|-\n| John Joslin\n| 1900\u20131902\n|-\n| Amos Odell\n| 1903\u20131904\n|-\n| Christopher Stinson\n| 1905\u20131907\n|-\n| Charles E. Ivens\n| 1908\u20131943\n|-\n| Harvey Cecil Odell\n| 1944\u20131967\n|-\n| Maxwell James Edgar