{"title_page": "Rural Municipality of South Cypress", "text_new": "The '''Rural Municipality of South Cypress''' is a former [[rural municipality]] (RM) in the [[Canada|Canadian]] [[Provinces and territories of Canada|province]] of Manitoba. It was originally incorporated as a rural municipality on December 22, 1883.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/municipalities/rural.shtml | title=Manitoba\u2019s Municipal History: Rural Municipalities and Local Government Districts | publisher=The Manitoba Historical Society | date=September 21, 2014 | accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref> It ceased on January 1, 2015 as a result of its [[Manitoba municipal amalgamations, 2015|provincially mandated]] [[Merger (politics)|amalgamation]] with the [[Glenboro, Manitoba|Village of Glenboro]] to form the [[Municipality of Glenboro \u2013 South Cypress]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/municipalities/amalgamations.shtml | title=Manitoba\u2019s Municipal History: Municipal Amalgamations (2015) | publisher=The Manitoba Historical Society | date=December 1, 2014 | accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe former RM is located in the [[Westman Region, Manitoba|Westman Region]] of the province and contains most of [[Spruce Woods Provincial Park]] and most of [[Provincial forests (Manitoba)|Spruce Woods Provincial Forest]]. The [[Canada 2006 Census|2006 census]] reported a population of 834.\n\n== Communities ==\n*Ashdown\n*Aweme\n*[[Glenboro, Manitoba|Glenboro]] (independent Village)\n*Skalholt\n*Stockton\n*[[Treesbank, Manitoba|Treesbank]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://glenboro.com/living/rm-of-south-cypress}}\n* [http://www.communityprofiles.mb.ca/cgi-bin/csd/index.cgi?id=4607038 South Cypress, MB Community Profile]\n* [http://geodepot.statcan.ca/GeoSearch2006/GeoSearch2006.jsp?resolution=H&lang=E&otherLang=F&census=Yes&DisplayData=Yes&NewImage=yes&layer=csd&IdentName=South%20Cypress%20(RM)&IdentUID=4607038 Map of South Cypress R.M. at Statcan]\n\n{{MBDivision7}}\n{{Manitoba|rural=yes}}\n\n{{coord|49|39|54|N|99|22|15|W|scale:500000|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Former rural municipalities in Manitoba|South Cypress]]\n[[Category:Populated places disestablished in 2015]]\n[[Category:2015 disestablishments in Manitoba]]\n{{Manitoba-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "The '''Rural Municipality of South Cypress''' is a former [[rural municipality]] (RM) in the [[Canada|Canadian]] [[Provinces and territories of Canada|province]] of Manitoba. It was originally incorporated as a rural municipality on December 22, 1883.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/municipalities/rural.shtml | title=Manitoba\u2019s Municipal History: Rural Municipalities and Local Government Districts | publisher=The Manitoba Historical Society | date=September 21, 2014 | accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref> It ceased on January 1, 2015 as a result of its [[Manitoba municipal amalgamations, 2015|provincially mandated]] [[Merger (politics)|amalgamation]] with the [[Glenboro, Manitoba|Village of Glenboro]] to form the [[Municipality of Glenboro \u2013 South Cypress]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mhs.mb.ca/docs/municipalities/amalgamations.shtml | title=Manitoba\u2019s Municipal History: Municipal Amalgamations (2015) | publisher=The Manitoba Historical Society | date=December 1, 2014 | accessdate=January 2, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe former RM is located in the [[Westman Region, Manitoba|Westman Region]] of the province and contains most of [[Spruce Woods Provincial Park]] and most of [[Provincial forests (Manitoba)|Spruce Woods Provincial Forest]]. The [[Canada 2006 Census|2006 census]] reported a population of 834.\n\n== Communities ==\n*Ashdown\n*Aweme\n*[[Glenboro, Manitoba|Glenboro]] (independent Village)\n*Skalholt\n*Stockton\n*[[Treesbank, Manitoba|Treesbank]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Official website|http://glenboro.com/living/rm-of-south-cypress}}\n* [http://www.